Table 1 provides information on the thermophysical characteristics of the nanofluid as well as the symbols utilized in the current research. When a surface is heated through convection, it is important to take into account the amount of heat that is lost through conduction, also known as Newtonian heating. It is also important to understand the behavior of the fluid close to the surface, which can be affected by the slip condition. This refers to how fluids behave when they come into contact with solid boundaries and can affect the rate at which the fluid moves near the surface. The extent of the slip is directly related to the amount of shear stress experienced by the fluid at the boundary75, 76. This understanding is crucial for accurately analyzing heat transfer through convection.Table 1
