				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\Theta$$\end{document}). However, if the temperature differences inside the stream are minimal, a significant simplification can be achieved. This means that the calculation process can be made easier if there are only small thermal variations within the stream. Under certain circumstances, the Rosseland Approximation formula can be simplified by substituting the variable Θ∞\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
