The Brinkman number is a dimensionless value that is used in the field of fluid mechanics to determine the importance of the viscous forces compared to the inertia forces within a fluid. It helps us understand how much the fluid's viscosity affects its behavior to its mass and movement. From Fig. 10a, the BM\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
